        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Cheering news from the United States</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Peach Point</placeName> <date when="1835-10-27">27th Oct 1835</date></p>
<p>Dr <persName>Brother</persName></p>

<p>We have heard nothing from you or the <persName>Boys</persName>, onley through the 
<persName>expresses </persName>tell <persName>Austin </persName>and <persName>Joel </persName>to write to us when they have an opportunety
as there <persName>mother </persName>is verry anxious to hear directly from them. <persName>Guy </persName>and<pb n="215"/>
<persName>Eliza </persName>have been verry sick but are now both well, the news from the<placeName> U S.</placeName>
is cheering. I hope the <persName>sixty five volenteers</persName> by the <placeName>Columbus </placeName>will reach you
in time <placeName>San antonio</placeName> once taken and then I think we have the <placeName>coast </placeName>clear
and will be able to keep it so our anxiety will be great untill we hear of
that place being taken which we hope with the protection of Provedence
you will be able to do. adue may the god of wars protect you</p>

<p><persName>James F. Perry</persName> [Rubric]</p>
<p>[Addressed:]<persName> Genl. S. F. Austin</persName> At <placeName>Camp</placeName></p>


        </div1>
